 Sunday. 5 west, about 140 miles south of Ponce, Puerto Rico, and 200 miles southeast of Santo Domingo. Tropical Storm Gilbert formed in the eastern Caribbean and strengthened into a hurricane Saturday night. m. There were no reports of casualties. Cabral said residents of the province of Barahona should closely follow Gilbert's movement. The storm was approaching from the southeast with sustained winds of 75 mph gusting to 92 mph.  Sunday at latitude 16. San Juan, on the north coast, had heavy rains and gusts Saturday, but they subsided during the night. 